.TH VEK_DOT_F32 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_dot_f32 \- dot product of two f32 vectors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "float vek_dot_f32(const float *" a ", const float *" b ", size_t " n ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_dot_f32 ()
computes the dot product of two single-precision floating-point vectors:
.PP
.RS
result = sum(a[i] * b[i]) for i = 0 to n-1
.RE
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.I a
First input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I b
Second input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I n
Number of elements. Must be greater than 0.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the dot product as a single-precision float.
.SH PERFORMANCE
O(n) with SIMD vectorization. On AVX-512, processes 16 floats per iteration
with 4 accumulators for instruction-level parallelism.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
float a[] = {1.0f, 2.0f, 3.0f};
float b[] = {4.0f, 5.0f, 6.0f};
float result = vek_dot_f32(a, b, 3);  // 32.0
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_l2sq_f32 (3),
.BR vek_cosine_f32 (3),
.BR vek_dot_i8 (3)
